  "body": "## env\r\n\r\nropsten testnet\r\n\r\n## test contract\r\n\r\n```sol\r\n//SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity 0.8.4;\r\n\r\ncontract Vault {\r\n    receive() external payable {\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function ethBalance()external view returns (uint balance){\r\n        return address(this).balance;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## test process\r\n\r\nstep1: send 1 wei to contract, named it `tx1`\r\nstep2: sleep 1 second (but `tx1` is not mined yet)\r\nstep3: while `tx1` is still in pending status, use `ethBalance()`  with `bind.CallOpts{Pending: true}` to call, get the pending balance.\r\n\r\nexpected: `ethBalance()` result 1 wei\r\nactually: result 0 wei\r\n\r\nso if it's 0 wei it makes no difference with `bind.CallOpts{Pending: false}` to call\r\n\r\nthe related code is at https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/0ba0b81e54483978ab823665afb627ab4999db06/accounts/abi/bind/base.go#L168",
